verbs.description: undraw (third-person singular simple present undraws, present participle undrawing, simple past undrew, past participle undrawn)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To draw aside or open; to pull back a layer of fabric, e.g. a curtain.
examples: She undrew the curtain to reveal the shining rays of the sun.

entries.meaning: (transitive) To clear or erase part of a drawing.
